 those proportional to\n$GMJ_2c^{-2}$, never put to the test so far. Most of the competing Newtonian\nsignals due to the classical multipoles of the planet's gravity field have\nquite different temporal signatures with respect to the post-Newtonian ones,\nmaking, thus, potentially easier disentangling them.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Oct 2018 13:49:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 18 Jan 2019 16:42:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 24 Jan 2019 17:44:35 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 18 Feb 2019 18:36:40 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 21 Feb 2019 20:54:40 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 2 Jul 2019 22:28:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-04"}
